comments: Not a super challenging course nor the most interesting, but glad I took it.
You learn all about the most contentious issues in the law, with a bunch of friends who want to do the same! Lots of fun debates.
a look at the way in which religion has interacted with the concept of government and human rights.

This is a great class. Professor Leaman is really nice, and you learn a lot of different topics related to religion, religious freedom, pluralism, and human rights (although it is rather West-centric, something that Prof. Leaman acknowledged at the beginning and that was mainly due to English source availibility).
